a(S'For the first time there was interest from collectors in Paris. In May Van Gogh completed what is generally considered his first major work, The Potato Eaters, the culmination of several years of work, painting peasant character studies.[44] In August his work was first exhibited in the windows of the paint dealer Leurs in The Hague. After one of his young peasant sitters became pregnant that September, Van Gogh was accused of forcing himself upon her[note 10] and the village priest forbade parishioners to model for him.[45]'
