a(S'Conflicts arose between the brothers. At the end of 1886, Theo found that living with Vincent was "almost unbearable". By early 1887, they were again at peace, and Vincent had moved to Asni res, a northwestern suburb of Paris, where he became acquainted with Signac. With  mile Bernard, he adopted elements of Pointillism, a technique in which a multitude of small coloured dots are applied to the canvas such that when seen from a distance they create an optical blend of hues. The style stresses the value of complementary colours including blue and orange to form vibrant contrasts that are enhanced when juxtaposed.[62]'
