a(S'As a young man, Van Gogh was interested in pursuing ministry to serve working people.[13][14] He studied for a time in the Netherlands but his zeal and self-imposed asceticism cost him a short-term position in lay ministry. He became somewhat embittered and rejected the church establishment, yet found a personal spirituality that was comforting and important to him.[14] By 1879, he made a shift in the direction of his life and found he could express his "love of God and man" through painting.[13]'
p3159
