a(S'Cinematography (from Greek:       , kinema "movements" and        , graphein "to record") is the science or art of motion-picture photography by recording light or other electromagnetic radiation, either electronically by means of an image sensor, or chemically by means of a light-sensitive material such as film stock.[1]'
