a(S'Origins and early history[edit]'
p7652
g2
tp7653
a(S'Main article: History of painting'
p7654
g2
tp7655
a(S'Like drawing, painting has its documented origins in caves and on rock faces. The finest examples, believed by some to be 32,000 years old, are in the Chauvet and Lascaux caves in southern France. In shades of red, brown, yellow and black, the paintings on the walls and ceilings are of bison, cattle, horses and deer.'
