a(S'In China, the art of printmaking developed some 1,100 years ago as illustrations alongside text cut in woodblocks for printing on paper. Initially images were mainly religious but in the Song Dynasty, artists began to cut landscapes. During the Ming (1368 1644) and Qing (1616 1911) dynasties, the technique was perfected for both religious and artistic engravings.[15][16]'
