a(S'Short: of the order of one second (1 Hz, 60 bpm, 10 100,000 audio cycles). Musical tempo is generally specified in the range 40 to 240 beats per minute. A continuous pulse cannot be perceived as a musical beat if it is faster than 8 10 per second (8 10 Hz, 480 600 bpm) or slower than 1 per 1.5 2 seconds (0.6 0.5 Hz, 40 30 bpm). Too fast a beat becomes a drone, too slow a succession of sounds seems unconnected (Fraisse 1956[page needed]; Woodrow 1951[page needed], both quoted in Covaciu-Pogorilowski n.d.). This time-frame roughly corresponds to the human heart rate and to the duration of a single step, syllable or rhythmic gesture.'
p9681
