a(S'Long:   many seconds or a minute, corresponding to a durational unit that "consists of musical phrases" (Moravcsik 2001, 114) which may make up a melody, a formal section, a poetic stanza or a characteristic sequence of dance moves and steps. Thus the temporal regularity of musical organisation includes the most elementary levels of musical form (MacPherson 1930, 3).'
