g2
tp10029
a(S'It was not that counterpoint was supplanted by harmony (Bach s tonal counterpoint is surely no less polyphonic than Palestrina s modal writing) but that an older type both of counterpoint and of vertical technique was succeeded by a newer type. And harmony comprises not only the (vertical ) structure of chords but also their (horizontal ) movement. Like music as a whole, harmony is a process.'
