a(S'Vibrato[edit]'
p10785
g2
tp10786
a(S'Vibrato is a technique in which a sustained note wavers very quickly and consistently between a higher and a lower pitch, giving the note a slight quaver. Vibrato is the pulse or wave in a sustained tone. Vibrato occurs naturally, and is the result of proper breath support and a relaxed vocal apparatus.[27] Some singers use vibrato as a means of expression. Many successful artists can sing a deep, rich vibrato.'
p10787
