a(S'Another influence came from the harmonic style of hymns of the church, which black slaves had learned and incorporated into their own music as spirituals.[31] The origins of the blues are undocumented, though they can be seen as the secular counterpart of the spirituals. However, as Gerhard Kubik points out, whereas the spirituals are homophonic, rural blues and early jazz "was largely based on concepts of heterophony."[32]'
