p17761
g2
tp17762
a(S'The study of the history of art is a relatively recent phenomenon; prior to the '
p17763
g2
tp17764
a(S'Renaissance, the modern concept of "art" did not exist. Over time, art '
p17765
g2
tp17766
a(S'historians have changed their views about what art is worthy of scrutiny. For '
p17767
g2
tp17768
a(S'example, during the early Victorian era, the 15th  century Italian artists were '
p17769
g2
tp17770
a(S'considered inferior to those of 16th  century High Renaissance. Such a '
p17771
g2
tp17772
a(S'notion was challenged by the Pre  Raphaelite movement. There has since '
p17773
g2
tp17774
a(S'been a trend, dominant in art history of the 21st century, to treat all cultures '
p17775
g2
tp17776
a(S'and periods neutrally. Thus, Australian Aboriginal art would not be deemed '
p17777
g2
tp17778
a(S'better or worse than Renaissance art it is just different. Art historical analysis '
p17779
g2
tp17780
a(S'has also evolved into studying the social and political use of art, rather than '
p17781
g2
tp17782
a(S'focusing solely on the aesthetic appreciation of its craftsmanship (beauty). '
