tp32679
a(g34
g32336
tp32680
a(S'Information on the "active" and "passive" panels may be used for constructing commands on the command line. Examples include current file, path to left panel, path to right panel, etc.'
p32681
g32336
tp32682
a(S'They provide a built-in viewer for (at least) the most basic file types.'
p32683
g32336
tp32684
a(S'They have a built-in editor. In many cases, the editor can extract certain elements of the panels into the text being edited.'
p32685
g32336
tp32686
a(S'Many support virtual file systems (VFS) such as viewing compressed archives, or working with files via an FTP connection.'
p32687
g32336
tp32688
a(S'They often have the word commander in the name, after Norton Commander.'
p32689
g32336
