a(S'A navigational file manager is a newer type of file manager. Since the advent of GUIs, it has become the dominant type of file manager for desktop computers.[citation needed]'
p32767
g32336
tp32768
a(g34
g32336
tp32769
a(S'Typically, it has two panes, with the filesystem tree in the left pane and the contents of the current directory in the right pane. For Mac OS X, one view in the Finder is an example of a navigational file manager.[dubious  discuss]'
