a(S'The first recorded uses of steganography can be traced back to 440 BC when Herodotus mentions two examples in his Histories.[3] Demaratus sent a warning about a forthcoming attack to Greece by writing it directly on the wooden backing of a wax tablet before applying its beeswax surface. Wax tablets were in common use then as reusable writing surfaces, sometimes used for shorthand.'
