tp33177
a(S'The art of concealing data in a puzzle can take advantage of the degrees of freedom in stating the puzzle, using the starting information to encode a key within the puzzle / puzzle image.'
p33178
g32336
tp33179
a(g34
g32336
tp33180
a(S'For instance, steganography using sudoku puzzles has as many keys as there are possible solutions of a sudoku puzzle, which is 6.71?1021. This is equivalent to around 70 bits, making it much stronger than the DES method, which uses a 56 bit key.[22]'
