a(S"File deletion is a way of removing a file from a computer's file system."
p33384
g32336
tp33385
a(g34
g32336
tp33386
a(S'Examples of reasons for deleting files are:'
p33387
g32336
tp33388
a(g34
g32336
tp33389
a(S'Freeing the disk space'
p33390
g32336
tp33391
a(S'Removing duplicate or unnecessary data to avoid confusion'
p33392
g32336
tp33393
a(S'Making sensitive information unavailable to others'
p33394
g32336
tp33395
a(S'All operating systems include commands for deleting files (rm on Unix, era in CP/M and DR-DOS, del/erase in MS-DOS/PC DOS, DR-DOS, Microsoft Windows etc.). File managers also provide a convenient way of deleting files. Files may be deleted one-by-one, or a whole directory tree may be deleted.'
