a(g34
g32336
tp35301
a(S'Internally, computers do not represent either hard disk drive or memory capacity in powers of 1,024, but reporting it in this manner is a convention.[91] The Microsoft Windows family of operating systems uses the binary convention when reporting storage capacity, so an HDD offered by its manufacturer as a 1 TB drive is reported by these operating systems as a 931 GB HDD. OS X 10.6 ("Snow Leopard") uses decimal convention when reporting HDD capacity.[91] The default behavior of the df command-line utility on Linux is to report the HDD capacity as a number of 1024-byte units.[92]'
p35302
