g32336
tp35741
a(S'The first character of the ls display indicates the file type and is not related to permissions. The remaining nine characters are in three sets, each representing a class of permissions as three characters. The first set represents the user class. The second set represents the group class. The third set represents the others class.'
p35742
g32336
tp35743
a(g34
g32336
tp35744
a(S'Each of the three characters represent the read, write, and execute permissions:'
